Here's a PlantUML component diagram capturing the static architecture of the NForge DevNote system, focusing on the general architectural concern:

```plantuml
@startuml nforge_devnote

[Express Server] as Server
[Socket.IO] as SocketIO
[Git Repository] as GitRepo
[User Management] as UserMgmt
[Wiki Functionality] as WikiFunc
[File Attachment] as FileAttach
[Real-time Collaboration] as RealTime
[Admin Tasks] as AdminTasks
[Localization] as Local
[Markdown Rendering] as MarkdownRender
[Configuration] as Config
[Core Logic] as CoreLogic
[Views] as Views
[Client-Side JS] as ClientJS

database "Git Data Store" as GitStore

Server - SocketIO
Server -- UserMgmt
Server -- WikiFunc
Server -- FileAttach
Server -- AdminTasks
Server -- Local
Server -- MarkdownRender
Server -- Config
Server -- CoreLogic
Server -- Views

UserMgmt -- GitRepo
WikiFunc -- GitRepo
FileAttach -- GitRepo
AdminTasks -- GitRepo

RealTime - SocketIO

GitRepo -- GitStore

ClientJS -- Server : HTTP/WebSocket

note right of CoreLogic
  Includes:
  - File utilities
  - Graph data structure
  - Renderer
  - i18n
  - Delta utilities
  - Test runner
end note

note right of ClientJS
  Includes:
  - jQuery
  - Bootstrap
  - CodeMirror
  - Underscore.js
  - Custom scripts
end note

@enduml
```